726506f-b.text:
Dry Harbor Road, west side, north of Penelope Avenue, showing in two views the Judge Jonathan T. Furman farmhouse from 1852 to 1873. This house, no longer standing in 1929, is said to have been erected in 1750. One Monkemeyer was the owner from 1891 to 1912. See other
views.
1922
View 2:April 1923
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection

726504f-a.text:
Dry Harbor Road, west side, between Penelope and 63rd Avenues, showing an old farmhouse, with stuckoed front, which was owned by M. Kuhlman (Kolmer) in 1909 and 1891. He also owned the house
directly south of this one.
July 2, 1935
P. L. Sperr

726503f-a.text:
Dry Harbor Road, north from Penelope Avenue, showing (left) an old farmhouse, which Armbruster believes, questionably,to be the Wright house of 1873. In 1909 it was owned by Kuhlman.
View 2 shows the same house, at a later date.
